description

This statewide orthoimagery dataset was acquired by the Texas Orthoimagery Program (TOP) and Surdex Corporation from October 2014 to January 2016. The majority of the moderate to heavy vegetation areas were acquired during leaf-off conditions. Aerial orthoimagery flown during leaf-off conditions allows the data user to 1) identify manmade features through the deciduous tree canopy and 2) distinguish between evergreen and deciduous vegetation. The entire dataset is available at 0.5-meter pixel resolution. This pixel resolution allows the user to identify detailed features on the ground such as cattle guards, extensions to housing, sidewalks and nature trails. The entire dataset is available as a 4-band (RGBIR) product which allows the user to display the imagery in natural color and color infrared. Flight date is in each filename as YYYYMMDD, and each image tile covers one 4th of a USGS Digital Orthophoto Quad (DOQ) resulting in a DOQQ or approximately 16 square miles with minimum 300-foot buffers. These TOP imagery products are also available as 4-band (RGBIR) natural color and color infrared compressed county mosaics (CCMs). CCMs are generated by compressing the DOQQ image tiles into a single mosaic per county. All individual tile images and the resulting mosaic are rectified in the UTM coordinate system, NAD 83, and cast into a single predetermined UTM zone. TOP is administered by the Texas Natural Resources Information System (TNRIS), a division of the Texas Water Development Board in Austin, Texas. The program was establish to support the TNRIS Strategic Mapping (StratMap) Program's goals for statewide basemap layers in Texas. TOP imagery are used for a wide variety of purposes throughout the state including land use planning, natural resource assessment, energy production, transportation, emergency management, ecology, air quality monitoring, etc. TOP acquisitions in Texas are contracted on an 'as needed' basis. Funding for this orthoimagery dataset was provided by four state entities. Surdex Corporation was selected under the 2009 - 2015 High Priority Imagery and Data Sets (HPIDS) state contract administered by the TNRIS StratMap Program. For this project, the TNRIS StratMap Program provided project coordination and management services. TNRIS also performed QA/QC which included inspection of interim and final orthoimagery products. Other links: https://www.surdex.net/

metadata

online mapping services

This dataset is available as an online mapping service. An OGC WMS service and an ArcGIS service are available. To connect to the WMS service in your software, please copy the unique url provided in the box below. To access the TNRIS ArcGIS Server, please use the following url in your ESRI software and select from the list of available services.

For questions regarding the use of one of these services in your software package, please consult the software help/support information.
https://imagery.tnris.org/server/services/TOP/TOP15_NCCIR_50cm/ImageServer/WMSServer

Listed shipping costs assume TNRIS provided hard drive. This price will vary if delivered on customer supplied hard drive.
If TNRIS provided drive is selected, the final total will include purchase cost of the drive.
Once a quote for your order has been completed, TNRIS will contact you for payment details.

Final cost for your order depends on many variables including hardware, staff time, computer time, data size, etc. TNRIS will contact you with the final, calculated cost. For a general estimate of your order, please take a look at the following prices:

Historical Imagery Costs

  • Research:
    • Full Historical Search (multiple years or sites): $60.00
    • Single Year Search (one site and one year): $30.00
    • Frame Search (customer must be able to identify specific frames needed): $15.00
  • Imagery:
    • Scanned Historical Frame: $10.00 per image
    • Scanned + Georeferenced Historical Frame: $20.00 per image

Bulk Collection Delivery Option

Customers have the option of ordering any collection that has already been scanned in full for the data size price (see Data Reproduction Costs), rather than paying by frame.

  • Staff Time: $46.00 per TB
  • Server/Computer Time: $0.15 per GB

Delivery Options and Policy

TNRIS requests 3-10 business days for data requests and product turn around. We do not accommodate any expedited orders.

  • Digital Download Delivery (0-10 GB): $7.00
  • TNRIS provided USB flash drive (64 GB): $40.00
  • TNRIS provided external hard drive (1 TB): $100.00
